  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PAYROLL SPECIALIST/ MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>The Payroll Specialist is responsible for end-to-end payroll processing across multiple entities and departments. This role ensures payroll accuracy, statutory compliance, effective payroll costing, budgeting, and alignment of\nsalary structures. The Payroll Specialist works closely with Finance, HR, and Management to deliver timely reporting, cost control, and payroll governance.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Payroll Operations</strong></p><p>Process and manage monthly payroll for multiple entities and departments\naccurately and on time Review andvalidate salary data before upload, ensuring\naccuracy of basic pay, allowances, deductions, overtime, bonuses, and\nincentives.</p><p>Ensure payroll uploads comply with internal policies and statutory requirements.</p><p>Handle payroll adjustments, back pay, salary revisions, and ad-hoc\npayments.</p><p><strong>Statutory Compliance & Reporting</strong></p><p>Ensure timely and accurate submission of:</p><p>CPF contributions</p><p>IRAS Form IR8A / Appendix 8A</p><p>MOM Manpower Survey</p><p>MOM Payroll / Salary Surveys (where applicable)</p><p>Stay updated on Singapore labour laws and statutory requirements related\nto payroll.</p><p>Liaise with CPF Board, IRAS, and MOM on payroll-related matters when\nrequired.</p><p><strong>Payroll Costing & Budget Management</strong></p><p>Perform detailed payroll costing by department, position, and entity.</p><p>Generate, maintain, and monitor payroll budgets for departments.</p><p>Track payroll expenses against approved budgets and highlight variances.</p><p>Support workforce cost planning and headcount budgeting.</p><p><strong>Salary Structure, Grading & Alignment</strong></p><p>Create and maintain salary grading structures and salary bands.</p><p>Review, re-look, and realign salary headers and components for positions.</p><p>Ensure internal equity and consistency in salary structures across\ndepartments and entities.</p><p>Support compensation reviews and job evaluations.</p><p><strong>Reporting & Management Support</strong></p><p>Prepare and submit monthly payroll reports to Finance and Management,\nincluding:</p><p>· Payroll summaries</p><p>· Departmental payroll cost reports</p><p>· Variance and trend analysis</p><p>Support payroll reconciliations, audits, and finance close activities.</p><p><strong>Process Improvement & Controls</strong></p><p>Review payroll processes and SOPs to enhance efficiency and accuracy.</p><p>Recommend and implement payroll best practices and internal controls.</p><p>Support payroll system improvements or enhancements.</p><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><p>Degree in Accounting, Finance, Human Resources, or related field.</p><p>Minimum <strong>5–7 years of relevant payroll experience</strong>, preferably\nmanaging multiple entities.</p><p>Strong knowledge of Singapore payroll regulations (CPF, IRAS, MOM).</p><p>Experience in payroll costing, budgeting, and salary structuring.</p><p>Proficient in payroll systems and Microsoft Excel.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
